                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d473">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1142</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gonzales</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-26T00:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1917, midnight</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Important developments military today were occupation of Camaguey City at noon by
                    Colonel Pujol; reestablishment there of civil government; advance of Pujol
                    toward Nuevitas, the only port in that province held by rebels, and decisive
                    defeat of a strong rebel force supposed to have been commanded by Gómez and
                    Colonel Collazo near southern coast on boundary line between Camaguey and Santa
                    Clara Province.</p>
                <p>Great delay in receipt of arms from the United States Government seems to be
                    hampering the President in pushing campaign.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
